    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>This plugin allow you to grab image from remote url and save into your own word press media library. By doing so, you never worried if the remote image was removed by its owner. This also save you steps to download the image to local computer and upload again to your own WordPress. There is also a JavaScript bookmarklet that helps to automate the process if you are surfing the internet and find something you would like to add to the library<\/p>\n<h4>Features<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Automatically downloads and adds the file to the media library.<\/li>\n<li>After the uploading is successful, you are redirected to the edit screen<\/li>\n<li>Once the bookmarklet is installed you don&#8217;t even need to copy and paste a url (just navigate to the url and select the bookmark).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Like this plugin? Please consider <a href=\"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/support\/view\/plugin-reviews\/lh-add-media-from-url\/\" rel=\"ugc\">leaving a 5-star review<\/a>.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>Love this plugin or want to help the LocalHero Project? Please consider <a href=\"https:\/\/lhero.org\/portfolio\/lh-add-media-from-url\/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">making a donation<\/a>.<\/strong><\/p>\n<h3>Translation credits<\/h3>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the entire <code>lh-add-media-from-url<\/code> folder to the <code>\/wp-content\/plugins\/<\/code> directory.<\/li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress.<\/li>\n<li>Go to Media-&gt;Add from Url to add media via url or use the bookmarklet.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<dt id='what%20is%20something%20does%20not%20work%3F'>\nWhat is something does not work?\n<\/h4>\n<p>\n<p>LH Add Media From Url, and all <a href=\"LocalHero\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https:\/\/lhero.org<\/a> plugins are made to WordPress standards. Therefore they should work with all well coded plugins and themes. However not all plugins and themes are well coded (and this includes many popular ones).<\/p>\n<p>If something does not work properly, firstly deactivate ALL other plugins and switch to one of the themes that come with core, e.g. twentyfifteen, twentysixteen etc.<\/p>\n<p>If the problem persists please leave a post in the support forum: <a href=\"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/support\/plugin\/lh-add-media-from-url\/\" rel=\"ugc\">https:\/\/wordpress.org\/support\/plugin\/lh-add-media-from-url\/<\/a>. I look there regularly and resolve most queries.<\/p>\n<\/p>\n<dt id='what%20if%20i%20need%20a%20feature%20that%20is%20not%20in%20the%20plugin%3F'>\nWhat if I need a feature that is not in the plugin?\n<\/h4>\n<p>\n<p>Please contact me for custom work and enhancements here: <a href=\"https:\/\/shawfactor.com\/contact\/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">https:\/\/shawfactor.com\/contact\/<\/a><\/p>\n<\/p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<p><strong>1.0 November 13, 2015<\/strong><br \/>\nInitial release.<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.05 March 10, 2016<\/strong><br \/>\nAdded documentation.<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.06 March 11, 2016<\/strong><br \/>\nMore documentation.<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.08 July 30, 2017<\/strong><br \/>\nRejigged upload handling.<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.09 July 30, 2017<\/strong><br \/>\nFile type fixes<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.10 July 30, 2017<\/strong><br \/>\nMoved uploader to separate class<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.11 August 03, 2017<\/strong><br \/>\nSeparate file<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.12 August 05, 2017<\/strong><br \/>\nlatest copy file class<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.13 September 13, 2017<\/strong><br \/>\ntranslatable strings<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.14 September 13, 2017<\/strong><br \/>\nadded language diectory<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.15 October 08, 2017<\/strong><br \/>\nUpdated lh-copy-from-url-class.php<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.20 March 05, 2021<\/strong><br \/>\nUpdated lh-copy-from-url-class.php again!<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.21 April 08, 2021<\/strong><br \/>\nAdded a filter to wp remote get<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.22 April 16, 2021<\/strong><br \/>\nBug Fix<\/p>\n<p><strong>1.23 January 15, 2024<\/strong><br \/>\nBug Fix<\/p>\n",
        "reviews": "<div class=\"review\">\n\t<div class=\"review-head\">\n\t\t<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"review-title\">Awesome<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"star-rating\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"reviewer\">\n\t\t\t\tBy <a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/daryadi\/\"><img alt='' src='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/0aaa256b774e054ac79f7294e951323e?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/0aaa256b774e054ac79f7294e951323e?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'\/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/daryadi\/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Daryadi <small>(daryadi)<\/small><\/a> on <span class=\"review-date\">December 8, 2022<\/span>\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class=\"review-body\">Awesome<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n\t<div class=\"review-head\">\n\t\t<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great!<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"star-rating\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"reviewer\">\n\t\t\t\tBy <a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/johannahrodgers\/\"><img alt='' src='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/6d73a6807c14b72329a0422a6a9e341d?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/6d73a6807c14b72329a0422a6a9e341d?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'\/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/johannahrodgers\/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">johannahrodgers<\/a> on <span class=\"review-date\">April 14, 2022<\/span>\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class=\"review-body\">Thank you!  This plugin works well.  I wish there was a way to add more than one link at a time.  Perhaps this already exists?  I will look around to see.<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n\t<div class=\"review-head\">\n\t\t<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"review-title\">It works. Here are some ideas for improvement<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"star-rating\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"4 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"4\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"><\/span><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"reviewer\">\n\t\t\t\tBy <a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/fissionblue\/\"><img alt='' src='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/6529e0f22abe6c9a76d3b0c45cfc80d2?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/6529e0f22abe6c9a76d3b0c45cfc80d2?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'\/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/fissionblue\/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">fissionblue<\/a> on <span class=\"review-date\">March 17, 2017<\/span>\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class=\"review-body\">No support for bulk uploads, i.e. 5 at a time.\n\nAlso, it takes you to the media page after successful upload. There should be a button \"Add from URL\" next to the factory button \"Add New\" at the top of this type of page.\n\nAdd these features, and you'll get my 5 stars. Great work.<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n\t<div class=\"review-head\">\n\t\t<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"review-title\">Gets the Job Done<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"star-rating\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"4 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"4\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"><\/span><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"reviewer\">\n\t\t\t\tBy <a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/pcpro178\/\"><img alt='' src='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/638bd1ebc937b09bf2d96a5fd4518a16?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/638bd1ebc937b09bf2d96a5fd4518a16?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'\/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/pcpro178\/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">pcpro178<\/a> on <span class=\"review-date\">January 25, 2017<\/span>\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class=\"review-body\">It gets the job done, but tighter integration with the media uploader would be nice, such as...\n\n1. On the Edit Media page, add at the top (next to the \"Add New\" button) an \"Add New from URL\" button.\n2. Get rid if the Add New from URL links altogether, and add an additional field for URL on the existing Add New \/ Upload New Media page.<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n\t<div class=\"review-head\">\n\t\t<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"review-title\">thanks<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"star-rating\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"reviewer\">\n\t\t\t\tBy <a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/mojtabafaal\/\"><img alt='' src='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/cdd3e0a18f5b80cb974430a086b0026e?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/cdd3e0a18f5b80cb974430a086b0026e?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'\/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/mojtabafaal\/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Mojtaba Faal <small>(MojtabaFaal)<\/small><\/a> on <span class=\"review-date\">November 29, 2016<\/span>\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class=\"review-body\">thanks<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n\t<div class=\"review-head\">\n\t\t<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"review-title\">A life saver<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"star-rating\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"reviewer\">\n\t\t\t\tBy <a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/thecianinator\/\"><img alt='' src='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/4b75e8e0f86b6d0d1a3d1f84faeefdcf?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/4b75e8e0f86b6d0d1a3d1f84faeefdcf?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'\/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/thecianinator\/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">thecianinator<\/a> on <span class=\"review-date\">September 3, 2016<\/span>\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class=\"review-body\"><p>I love this plugin. It has saved me so much time. The ability to go directly to Media and add images from a URL is great. No convoluted menu navigation required. URL must have a .jpg extension though, as is stated in the plugin information. I would recommend this plugin; overall, it's good.\n<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n\t<div class=\"review-head\">\n\t\t<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"review-title\">It nearly works<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"star-rating\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"4 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"4\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"><\/span><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"reviewer\">\n\t\t\t\tBy <a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/lucrus\/\"><img alt='' src='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/ebecc8a54ecb651d53f7595ccb5e48d6?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/ebecc8a54ecb651d53f7595ccb5e48d6?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'\/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/lucrus\/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">lucrus<\/a> on <span class=\"review-date\">September 3, 2016<\/span>\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class=\"review-body\"><p>It does not work when the URL contains spaces. Luckily I can change the URL so I can workaround the issue, but it would be much better if it worked out of the box with any valid URL. Five stars if you fix it.\n<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n"
    },
    "short_description": "Upload files from an url to wordpress media library, either enter file urls in an onsite input box or click a bookmarklet.",
    "description": "<p>This plugin allow you to grab image from remote url and save into your own word press media library. By doing so, you never worried if the remote image was removed by its owner. This also save you steps to download the image to local computer and upload again to your own WordPress. There is also a JavaScript bookmarklet that helps to automate the process if you are surfing the internet and find something you would like to add to the library<\/p>\n<h4>Features<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Automatically downloads and adds the file to the media library.<\/li>\n<li>After the uploading is successful, you are redirected to the edit screen<\/li>\n<li>Once the bookmarklet is installed you don&#8217;t even need to copy and paste a url (just navigate to the url and select the bookmark).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Like this plugin? Please consider <a href=\"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/support\/view\/plugin-reviews\/lh-add-media-from-url\/\" rel=\"ugc\">leaving a 5-star review<\/a>.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>Love this plugin or want to help the LocalHero Project? Please consider <a href=\"https:\/\/lhero.org\/portfolio\/lh-add-media-from-url\/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">making a donation<\/a>.<\/strong><\/p>\n<h3>Translation credits<\/h3>\n",
